headline: Teradyne Stock Is the Top Performer in the S&P 500. Here’s Why.
summary: Teradyne  stock surged double digits on Wednesday after the maker of semiconductor test equipment posted better-than-expected earnings in the second quarter.  Shares surged 19% to $107.96, putting the stock on pace for its highest close since March 7, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  The sharp gains came after  Teradyne  posted second-quarter earnings on Tuesday that surpassed expectations.
